## TABLE: MSBK_BUS_DTL (PostgreSQL-compatible, called MADB internally)

Columns and their meaning:

| Column            | Type        | Description                                      |
|-------------------|-------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| MSBK_BUS_DTL_ID   | BIGINT PK   | Unique row ID                                    |
| BUS_DATE          | DATE        | Business date of the reconciliation run          |
| MSBK_ID           | BIGINT      | Master book ID (links to the book being recon'd) |
| REC_ID            | BIGINT      | Reconciliation ID                                |
| REC_SUBCATEGORY_ID| BIGINT      | Reconciliation sub-category ID                   |
| STATUS            | VARCHAR     | Job status: COMPLETE, PROCESSING, PENDING, FAILED|
| EXPN              | VARCHAR     | Explanation / rec type (e.g. CATS-vs-MOTIF)      |
| EXPNCOUNT         | INT         | Number of exceptions / breaks found              |
| START_TIME        | TIMESTAMP   | When processing started                          |
| END_TIME          | TIMESTAMP   | When processing ended (null if still running)    |
| SERVICE_NAME      | VARCHAR     | Service that processed it (e.g. FOBO Service)    |
| ISHOLIDAY         | CHAR(1)     | 'Y' or 'N' — whether BUS_DATE is a holiday       |
| REGN_ID           | VARCHAR     | Region: APAC, EMEA, AMER                         |
| IN_MOTIF          | CHAR(1)     | 'Y' or 'N' — whether book exists in MOTIF system |
| BUSINESSAREANAME  | VARCHAR     | Business area name (e.g. FI Credit, Municipals)  |
| HIERARCHYLEVEL    | VARCHAR     | Hierarchy level name (e.g. EM LATAM, US HG)      |
| HIERARCHYLEVEL7   | VARCHAR     | Sub-hierarchy level 7 detail                     |
| LASTUPDATE        | TIMESTAMP   | When this row was last updated                   |
| LASTUPDATEDBY     | VARCHAR     | User or service that last updated this row       |

