## WHAT TO BUILD

A single-page React + TypeScript dashboard with these sections:

### 1. Top KPI Bar (6 cards)
Show counts for: COMPLETE | PROCESSING | PENDING | FAILED | HOLIDAY (ISHOLIDAY=Y) | IN_MOTIF (IN_MOTIF=Y)
Each card shows: count + label. Use color only in text and left border accent (3px). White card background.

### 2. Filter Bar
Dropdowns to filter the table by:
- STATUS (All / COMPLETE / PROCESSING / PENDING / FAILED)
- REGN_ID (All / APAC / EMEA / AMER)
- ISHOLIDAY (All / Y / N)
- IN_MOTIF (All / Y / N)
- BUS_DATE (date picker or text input)
- BUSINESSAREANAME (dropdown, populated from data)
Live filter — updates table instantly as user changes dropdowns.

### 3. Main Data Table
Columns to show (in this order):
MSBK_BUS_DTL_ID | BUS_DATE | MSBK_ID | REGN_ID | BUSINESSAREANAME | HIERARCHYLEVEL | HIERARCHYLEVEL7 | STATUS | EXPN | EXPNCOUNT | START_TIME | END_TIME | Duration | ISHOLIDAY | IN_MOTIF | LASTUPDATEDBY | LASTUPDATE

Rules:
- STATUS: render as a colored badge (COMPLETE=green, PROCESSING=blue, PENDING=amber, FAILED=red). Color in text and border only, white/near-white background.
- REGN_ID: render as a small region badge (APAC=blue, EMEA=green, AMER=purple).
- ISHOLIDAY / IN_MOTIF: render Y/N as small badges.
- Duration: calculate as END_TIME - START_TIME. Show as "Xm Ys". If END_TIME is null, show elapsed since START_TIME with a live blinking indicator.
- EXPNCOUNT: if > 0 show in amber, if 0 show muted grey.
- Timestamps: format as "DD MMM HH:mm:ss".
- Clicking any row opens a side drawer showing all fields for that row in a clean label/value layout.
- Table is sortable on all columns. Click column header to sort asc/desc.
- Show total row count below filter bar.

### 4. Summary Charts (below table)
Three horizontal bar charts side by side:
- Jobs by REGN_ID
- Jobs by STATUS
- Jobs by BUSINESSAREANAME (top 10)
Use CSS bars only — no chart library needed. Show count and percentage label on each bar.

